<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="36.[264,1324,457,1683]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,409,457,483]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Description</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[428,491,457,483]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Male</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[511,574,458,483]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Head</emphasis>
. Front silvery tomentose, a few white hairs present; antenna black; scape and pedicel with white hair, shorter dark hair near apex of pedicel; first flagellomere narrow, evenly tapering from base to acuminate apex; antennal ratio: 
<number box="[1240,1257,537,563]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="7.0">7</number>
: 
<number box="[1262,1280,537,563]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="4.0">4</number>
: 
<number box="[1284,1318,537,563]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="21.0">21</number>
; face white pilose and tomentose, bare medially, tomentum next to eye margin; oral margin dusky (appears pale in some lights); proboscis projects beyond oral margin for a distance approximately twice head height; gena white pilose and tomentose; occiput white pilose, tomentum white, restricted to lower half of occiput; vertex and ocellar tubercle with darker, not black, hair.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[264,1324,457,1683]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis box="[312,396,778,803]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Thorax</emphasis>
. Mesonotum black, side and anterior margin cinereous pollinose; median longitudinal stripe cinereous, broad, not reaching transverse suture; notum white pilose, tomentum yellow, scattered; pleura white pilose and tomentose; legs black, white pilose and tomentose; hind tibia brownish; halter with stem and knob yellowish; scutellum white pilose, tomentum yellow, scattered.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[264,1324,457,1683]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis box="[312,370,978,1003]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Wing</emphasis>
. Very faintly infumate (at least not entirely hyaline); venation normal; crossvein r­m slightly beyond middle of cell dm; crossvein m­cu sinuous; basicosta with white hair.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[264,1324,457,1683]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis box="[312,422,1058,1083]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Abdomen</emphasis>
. White pilose and tomentose, the latter pale yellow on dorsum; tergites with lateral margins narrowly pale; sternites with posterior margins narrowly pale.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[264,1324,457,1683]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis box="[312,422,1138,1163]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[440,527,1137,1163]" captionStart="FIGURES 42 – 45" captionStartId="37.[264,382,1744,1768]" captionTargetBox="[327,1255,636,1719]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[316,1273,632,1721]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURES 42 – 45. Geron male genitalia. 42, G. johnsoni Painter; a, lateral view; b, tip of gonocoxa, ventral view. 43, G. monticola Hall &amp; Evenhuis, sp. nov.; a, lateral view; b, gonocoxa, dorsal view. 44, G. nevadensis Hall &amp; Evenhuis, sp. nov.; a, lateral view; b, tip of gonocoxa, dorsal view. 45, G. nigripes Painter; a, lateral view; b, gonocoxa, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/156853/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
Fig. 
<number box="[496,527,1137,1163]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="42.0">42</number>
</figureCitation>
) with gonocoxa in ventral view flat, without depressions or ridges, in lateral view rectangular, lower margin with a small protuberance near apex; gonostylus long, narrow, about four times longer than high, rounded apically; lateral ramus narrow slightly curved, acuminate apically, shorter than gonostylus; dorsolateral ramus large, broad, nearly equal in length to gonostylus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[264,1324,457,1683]" box="[312,541,1337,1363]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,403,1337,1363]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Female</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[264,1324,457,1683]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,382,1377,1403]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<typeStatus box="[312,382,1377,1403]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Types</typeStatus>
</emphasis>
. 
<typeStatus box="[400,509,1377,1403]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Holotype</typeStatus>
male (Horseneck Beach, Massachusetts, 
<date box="[1001,1137,1377,1403]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="1913-07-30">
<number box="[1001,1033,1377,1403]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="30.0">30</number>
.vii. 
<number box="[1075,1137,1377,1403]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="1913.0">1913</number>
</date>
, C.W. Johnson) deposited in 
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:33791" box="[420,484,1417,1443]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:33791" name="Museum of Comparative Zoology" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">MCZ</collectionCode>
(No. 
<number box="[558,637,1417,1443]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="27266.0">27266</number>
). The 
<typeStatus box="[715,765,1417,1443]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">type</typeStatus>
is in fair condition, with the dorsum partially abraded and the middle legs missing. The genitalia have been dissected and placed in a microvial attached to the pin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[312,1078,1537,1563]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="36.[264,1324,457,1683]" box="[312,1078,1537,1563]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,404,1537,1563]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Biology</emphasis>
. Immature stages and adult flower preferences unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="36.[264,1324,457,1683]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,444,1577,1603]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Discussion</emphasis>
. Known only from two males. The original description states that the hair on the pedicel is black. In actuality, the hair in the 
<typeStatus box="[855,906,1617,1643]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">type</typeStatus>
is more brownish than black.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
